# AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store - Secrets Configuration
# 
# This file defines all secrets that will be injected into AWS SSM Parameter Store.
# Copy this file to .env.ssm and replace placeholder values with actual secrets.
#
# Usage:
#   1. Copy: cp .env.ssm.example .env.ssm
#   2. Edit .env.ssm with your actual secrets
#   3. Run: ./scripts/bootstrap/06-inject-ssm-parameters.sh
#
# Format:
#   /path/to/parameter=value
#
# Notes:
#   - All parameters are created as SecureString (encrypted at rest)
#   - Parameters can be updated by running the script again
#   - .env.ssm is gitignored for security

# ============================================================================
# Kagent Service (Intelligence Platform)
# ============================================================================
/zerotouch/prod/kagent/openai_api_key=sk-your-openai-api-key-here

# ============================================================================
# Agent Executor Service
# ============================================================================

# NOTE: PostgreSQL and Dragonfly credentials are managed by Crossplane claims
# and automatically provisioned. No manual configuration needed.

# LLM API Keys
/zerotouch/prod/agent-executor/openai_api_key=sk-your-openai-api-key-here
/zerotouch/prod/agent-executor/anthropic_api_key=sk-ant-your-anthropic-api-key-here

# ============================================================================
# Platform-Wide Secrets (Shared Across Services)
# ============================================================================

# GitHub Container Registry (GHCR) Credentials
# Used for pulling private container images from ghcr.io
# Generate token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens (with read:packages scope)
/zerotouch/prod/platform/ghcr/username=your-github-username
/zerotouch/prod/platform/ghcr/password=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# GitHub Repository Access (for ArgoCD)
# Used by ArgoCD to access private Git repositories (e.g., zerotouch-tenants)
# Generate token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens (with repo scope)
# NOTE: Can use the same token as GHCR if it has both read:packages and repo scopes
/zerotouch/prod/platform/github/username=your-github-username
/zerotouch/prod/platform/github/token=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# Private Git Repositories (for ArgoCD - Legacy/Bootstrap Script)
# List of private repositories that ArgoCD needs access to
# Format: One repository URL per line, prefixed with ARGOCD_PRIVATE_REPO_
# The bootstrap script (07-add-private-repo.sh) will automatically add these to ArgoCD
# NOTE: For production, use the ArgoCD Repository Credentials section below (ESO-managed)
ARGOCD_PRIVATE_REPO_1=https://github.com/your-org/zerotouch-tenants.git
ARGOCD_PRIVATE_REPO_2=https://github.com/your-org/your-tenant-repo.git
# Add more as needed: ARGOCD_PRIVATE_REPO_3, ARGOCD_PRIVATE_REPO_4, etc.

# ============================================================================
# ArgoCD Repository Credentials (for ExternalSecrets - Recommended)
# ============================================================================
# These credentials are managed by External Secrets Operator (ESO) and stored
# in AWS SSM Parameter Store. ESO automatically creates and syncs Kubernetes
# secrets for ArgoCD repository access.
#
# Benefits over manual secrets:
#   - Automatic rotation and sync
#   - Centralized secret management in AWS SSM
#   - No manual kubectl secret creation needed
#   - Audit trail in AWS CloudTrail

# Tenant Registry Repository
# This is the main registry that contains:
#   - tenants/*/config.yaml (tenant configurations)
#   - repositories/*.yaml (tenant repo credential manifests)
# Used by: bootstrap/components/argocd-repo-registry.yaml
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/zerotouch-tenants/url=https://github.com/your-org/zerotouch-tenants.git
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/zerotouch-tenants/username=your-github-username
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/zerotouch-tenants/password=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# Tenant Repository: Example Tenant
# This is the actual tenant workload repository containing Kubernetes manifests
# Used by: repositories/repo-example-tenant.yaml in tenant registry
# Pattern: /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/<tenant-name>/{url,username,password}
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/example-tenant/url=https://github.com/your-org/example-tenant.git
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/example-tenant/username=your-github-username
/zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/example-tenant/password=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# Add more tenant repositories following the same pattern:
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/<tenant-name>/url=https://github.com/org/repo.git
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/<tenant-name>/username=username
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/<tenant-name>/password=token
#
# Example for a second tenant:
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/acme-corp/url=https://github.com/acme-corp/manifests.git
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/acme-corp/username=acme-bot
# /zerotouch/prod/argocd/repos/acme-corp/password=ghp_acme_token_here

